<h1>Data Visualization</h1>

<div class="content-box">
<p>
Data visualization is the graphical representation of data to understand patterns, trends,
distributions, and anomalies. Visual tools such as histograms and box plots help transform
raw numerical data into meaningful insights.
</p>
</div>

<h2>Histogram</h2>

<div class="content-box">
<p>
A histogram represents the frequency distribution of continuous data.
Data is grouped into class intervals, and rectangles are drawn whose heights represent frequencies.
</p>

<h3>Example: Marks Obtained</h3>
<p>Marks: 40, 45, 50, 55, 60, 60, 65, 70, 75, 80</p>

<h3>Histogram Representation</h3>

<div class="histogram-wrapper">
    <div class="y-axis">Frequency</div>

    <div class="chart">
        <div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:70px;">2</div>
            <div class="label">40–50</div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:110px;">3</div>
            <div class="label">50–60</div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:110px;">3</div>
            <div class="label">60–70</div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="bar" style="height:70px;">2</div>
            <div class="label">70–80</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="x-axis">Marks</div>
</div>

<h3>Applications of Histogram</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Analyzing data distribution</li>
    <li>Identifying skewness</li>
    <li>Quality control in manufacturing</li>
    <li>Performance analysis in engineering systems</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Box Plot</h2>

<div class="content-box">
<p>
A box plot (box-and-whisker plot) represents data using the five-number summary:
minimum, Q₁, median, Q₃, and maximum.
</p>

<h3>Example Dataset</h3>
<p>Data: 10, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40, 45</p>

<h3>Box Plot Representation</h3>

<div class="boxplot">
    <div class="line"></div>

    <div class="point" style="left:0px;"></div>
    <div class="box-label" style="left:0px;">Min</div>

    <div class="box" style="left:90px; width:220px;"></div>
    <div class="box-label" style="left:90px;">Q₁</div>
    <div class="box-label" style="left:290px;">Q₃</div>

    <div class="median" style="left:200px;"></div>
    <div class="box-label" style="left:180px;">Median</div>

    <div class="point" style="left:410px;"></div>
    <div class="box-label" style="left:395px;">Max</div>
</div>

<h3>Applications of Box Plot</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Detecting outliers</li>
    <li>Comparing multiple datasets</li>
    <li>Understanding data spread and symmetry</li>
    <li>Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) in ML</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="content-box">
<h2>Engineering and Data Science Applications</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Performance analysis and response time evaluation</li>
    <li>Income and demand analysis</li>
    <li>Feature distribution analysis in Machine Learning</li>
    <li>Network traffic and latency modeling</li>
</ul>
</div>

